    • getMaximumPixelSpacing

      public float getMaximumPixelSpacing()
      Get the maxmimum allowed resolution value.

      This is a value in mm. Any values greater than this is not allowed, as it is considered to be a sufficient resolution for accurate measurments.

      Returns:
      The resolution in distance between one pixel and the next.

    • setMagnification

    • setDistance

      public void setDistance(String SID, String SOD)
      Sets patient to detector and patient to x-ray source distances. Distances are measeured from the midsagittal plane for lateral cephs, and transmeatal axis (ear rods) for PA cephs. Detector is either the film or the digitizing detector, in the case of digital x-ray machines.
      Parameters:
      SID - Source to Detector distance in mm.
      SOD - X-ray source to Patient distance in mm.

    • setPosteroAnterior

      public void setPosteroAnterior()
      A shortcut for standard postero-anterior cephalograms. Sets:
      • Primary Angle: 180
      • Secondary Angle: 0
      • View Code: SNM3 R-10214 postero-anterior

    • setAnteroPosterior

      public void setAnteroPosterior()
      A shortcut for standard antero-posterior cephalograms. Sets:
      • Primary Angle: 0
      • Secondary Angle: 0
      • View Code: SNM3 R-10206 antero-posterior

    • setRightLateral

      public void setRightLateral()
      A shortcut for standard right-lateral cephalograms. Sets:
      • Primary Angle: -90
      • Secondary Angle: 0
      • View Code: SNM3 R-10232 right lateral

    • setLeftLateral

      public void setLeftLateral()
      A shortcut for standard left-lateral cephalograms.
      • Primary Angle: +90
      • Secondary Angle: 0
      • View Code: SNM3 R-10236 left lateral

    • writeDCM

      public File writeDCM()
      Write this Cephalogram in a DICOM .dcm file.

      Before writing, checks the validity of the object. The output file will have the same name as the input image file of this Cephalogram, with its extension replaced with .dcm and in the same folder.

      Returns:
      The File this object was written to, or null if the object was not written because of its invalidiy
      See Also:
      • validate(ValidationContext, ValidationResult)

    • writeDCM

      filename - The new filename of the file. Can be null in which case the the value returne by getDCMFileName() will be used.
